Project CODERUNNER - Version One - 15 Mar 2026

This is a CGI FORM for running Code. 

There is mainly a FORM. And some radio buttons to select the programming 
language. And then a RUN button.

That is all.

The output is displayed below the HTML. There are several options. There is a 
way to pass arguments (to the code, not the binaries).

Requirements

Any wanted language to use is expected to be be installed and available as a 
single binary. And, of course, a LOCALHOST server able to run .cgi code in a 
directory.

Installation

Just place all the code somewhere nice within your LOCALHOST server's space.

Example

    http://localhost/coderun/coderun.cgi

Know Bugs

The default is to display output after the HTML - there was supposed to be a 
way to display the output before that HTML...

Proble more.
